```

Note that you cannot use `null` as a default value for a value type (`Vector3` in this case) unless it is defined as a nullable value type. If `Vector3` is a value type, you can make it nullable by using `Nullable<Vector3>` or shorthand `Vector3?`:

```csharp
public void UpdateFollowerCamPos(Vector3? EulerRotOffset = null) 
{
    // Method implementation
}
```

By making `Vector3?` nullable, you can now set `null` as a default value for the method argument.

